description: A Neolithic barrow which appears to have been a focus of attention during the Roman period. Nearby depositions of mortarium, coins, and votive leafs lead the excavators to identify this is as a possible shrine through out the Roman period.
bibliography: Hey, Gill, Caroline Dennis, and Andrew Mayes. “Archaeological Investigations on Whiteleaf Hill, Princes Risborough.” Records of Buckinghamshire 47 (2023): 380. https://doi.org/10.5284/1115801.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Whiteleaf Hill, Princes Risborough (Buckinghamshire).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
